2026-06-19 09:23:36,260 DEBUG Tool call: submit_final_result({'final_result': '## Answer: Amazon (AMZN) plans to spend the most in capex in 2025.\n\n### Detailed Analysis\n\nBased on the most recent official guidance provided by each company as of April 7, 2025, here are the planned 2025 capital expenditures:\n\n| Company | Ticker | 2025 Capex Plan | Source |\n|---------|--------|----------------|--------|\n| **Amazon** | **AMZN** | **~$100–105 billion** | CEO Andy Jassy & CFO Brian Olsavsky on Q4 2024 earnings call (Feb 6, 2025) |\n| **Alphabet (Google)** | **GOOG** | **~$75 billion** | CEO Sundar Pichai on Q4 2024 earnings call (Feb 4, 2025) |\n| **Meta (Meta)** | **META** | **$60–65 billion** | CEO Mark Zuckerberg on Q4 2024 earnings call (Jan 29, 2025) |\n\n### Breakdown\n\n1. **Amazon (AMZN)** – ~$100–105 billion: On their Q4 2024 earnings call (February 6, 2025), CEO Andy Jassy announced plans to spend $100 billion on capital expenditures in 2025, calling it a "once-in-a-lifetime type of business opportunity." CFO Brian Olsavsky noted that Q4 2024 capex of $26.3 billion would be "reasonably representative" of the 2025 quarterly run rate, implying approximately $105 billion for the full year. The vast majority of this spending is directed toward AI infrastructure for AWS.\n\n2. **Alphabet/Google (GOOG)** – ~$75 billion: On their Q4 2024 earnings call (February 4, 2025), CEO Sundar Pichai stated the company expects to invest approximately $75 billion in capital expenditures in 2025, primarily for AI and technical infrastructure including data centers and servers.\n\n3. **Meta (META)** – $60–65 billion: CEO Mark Zuckerberg announced in a Facebook post (January 24, 2025) and confirmed on the Q4 2024 earnings call (January 29, 2025) that Meta plans to invest between $60 billion and $65 billion in capital expenditures in 2025, with most of the investment going toward AI infrastructure and data centers.\n\n### Conclusion\n\n**Amazon (AMZN)** plans to spend the most on capital expenditures in 2025, with guidance of approximately **$100–105 billion**. This significantly exceeds Alphabet/Google\'s ~$75 billion and Meta\'s $60–65 billion. \n\n### Sources\n\n{\n    "sources": [\n        {\n            "url": "https://www.cnbc.com/2025/02/06/amazon-expects-to-spend-100-billion-on-capital-expenditures-in-2025.html",\n            "name": "CNBC - Amazon expects to spend $100 billion on capital expenditures in 2025"\n        },\n        {\n            "url": "https://www.cnbc.com/2025/02/04/alphabet-expects-to-invest-about-75-billion-in-capex-in-2025.html",\n            "name": "CNBC - Alphabet will invest about $75 billion in capital expenditures in 2025"\n        },\n        {\n            "url": "https://finance.yahoo.com/news/meta-platforms-inc-meta-q4-072528195.html",\n            "name": "Yahoo Finance - Meta Platforms Inc (META) Q4 2024 Earnings Call Highlights"\n        },\n        {\n            "url": "https://sherwood.news/business/amazon-plans-100-billion-spend-on-ai-in-2025",\n            "name": "Sherwood News - Amazon plans on spending more than $100 billion on capex in 2025"\n        },\n        {\n            "url": "https://markets.businessinsider.com/news/stocks/amazon-bets-big-on-ai-with-100b-planned-capex-in-2025-1034325820",\n            "name": "Markets Insider - Amazon Bets Big on AI With $100B Planned Capex in 2025"\n        },\n        {\n            "url": "https://www.businessinsider.com/amazon-earnings-call-report-amzn-stock-live-updates-2025-2",\n            "name": "Business Insider - Amazon Earnings Recap: CFO indicates ~$105 billion in capex"\n        },\n        {\n            "url": "https://finance.yahoo.com/news/hyperscaler-capex-reach-300-billion-200930863.html",\n            "name": "Yahoo Finance - Hyperscaler Capex to Reach $300 Billion in 2025: Morgan Stanley"\n        }\n    ]\n}'})
